comments.body:
@kponichtera Yes buildah's distrubuted cache is different from docker and more in line with how distributed cache works in kaniko, it is due to how buildah intermediate caching mechanism is designed. The kaniko and buildah's method have their own perks i.e parent image is not inflated with intermediate images, intermediate images are truly distributed ( can be kept in different registry or same as well ), two different images don't need to carry same intermediate image.

 > Doing it this way not only requires a separate repo

 No it does not needs a different repo, all intermediate image can be kept in the same repo but they will have different tags

 @kponichtera However i agree with you that difference need to be documented hence I created a PR: https://github.com/containers/buildah/pull/4644 and maybe in future maybe buildah could support both its original cache mechanism and buildkit's model as well.
